This paper deals with the problem of multi-hop scheduling in self-backhauled millimeter wave (mmWave) networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also addresses the problem of rate allocation subject to latency constraints, which is related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper proposes a new system design that factors in mmWave-specific channel variations and network dynamics, which involves system modeling and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. The paper also uses reinforcement learning to learn the best paths, which is related to artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with millimeter wave networks, which is a topic related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category.
